text: Sir Nathaniel Rahumaea Waena GCMG, CSI, KStJ (born 1 November 1945) was the Governor-General of Solomon Islands from 2004 to 2009. Waena was a Member of the National Parliament from 1984 to 2004.List of members of the Third Parliament (see also lists for Fourth, Fifth, Sixth, and Seventh Parliaments). ==References== Category:Living people Category:Governors-General of Solomon Islands Category:1945 births
